HEADWORD: Making-up
<hw>Mak"ing-up`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of bringing spirits to a certain degree of strength, called
<xex>proof</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of becoming reconciled or
friendly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mako</ent>⟦br⟧
